The paper discusses the development of a benchmark platform for evaluating efficient storage techniques for RDF data and evaluation strategies for SPARQL queries. This falls under the domain of database systems (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as RDF data and SPARQL queries are commonly used in knowledge representation and reasoning tasks. The paper also mentions the use of social-world distributions and access patterns, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and deep learning (cs.DL) research. Finally, the paper evaluates existing engines, which falls under the domain of software engineering (cs.SE).
